Good news: there is a wonder-world of fresh grown foods awaiting those who do not have the space to grow a garden. Those who cannot afford high-priced supplements can have access to the most nutrient dense foods on the planet for just pennies a meal. Listen, watch, and learn how you can supply all of the latest super-nutrients your body needs with little time, and little expense.

chapters.title: All brassicas are an excellent source of sulphur, an important mineral for its cleansing and antiseptic effect, on the blood and digestive systems. Sulphur is essential for healthy hair, nails and skin, and for protein and carbohydrate absorption

H. pylori causes a condition called gastritis, which enormously increases a person's risk of stomach cancer. Sulforaphane kills H.pylori. The compound can be found in small amounts in regular, mature broccoli. But broccoli sprouts are by far the best source.

Iron: Vital for the formation of red blood cells. Builds up the quality of the blood. Increases the resistance to stress and disease. Attracts oxygen to the body and carries it to all systems, tissues and organs. Improves circulation, digestion, elimination, and respiration. Improves reasoning ability and memory.
Vitamin B1: For healthy muscle tone and growth. Helps all kinds of stress. Preserves the health of the nervous system, muscles and heart. Provides energy. Improves learning capacity
Vitamin B2: Needed for the cell respiration. Necessary for the formation of red blood cells and antibodies. Benefits vistion. Promotes healthy skin, nails, and hair. Helps in stress situations

Vitamin B2: Assists in the metabolism and utilization of proteins, fats, and carbohydrates, Promotes a healthy digestive system. Necessary for the health of the skin and tongue. Essential for the body's production of cortisone, thyroxine, insulin, and other hormones. Necessary for healthy nervous system and brain function. Increases circulation and reduces cholesterol.
